    <description>This 47-card expansion for Nuclear War is packaged in 8-card booster packs (inspired by the success Magic: The Gathering).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The cards appear different numbers of times on the press sheet, giving different levels of &amp;quot;rarity&amp;quot;, and the boosters are more or less random. They are packed in clear plastic, with a cover/proof of purchase card (40 of the proof of purchase cards can be sent in for a free Supergerm T-shirt).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The new cards are mostly Secrets (20) and Specials (19), with three new sizes of Propaganda, four new sizes of Warhead, and one new Delivery System.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To incorporate this expansion into an existing Nuclear War/Escalation/Proliferation deck while preserving the existing balance of card types and strengths requires using a bunch of the new Propaganda and Warhead cards; to preserve the proportion of delivery systems, you either have to use a lot of the Delta Clipper or scavenge some extra &amp;quot;regular&amp;quot; delivery systems (perhaps a use for the ads/jokers from Nuclear War, or some of the blanks available from Flying Buffalo).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Expands:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Nuclear War&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Microbadge&amp;#10;&amp;#10; Buy It&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
